43
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:20,420
♫ The baby is left alone at home ♫

44
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:41,780
I must be out of my mind.

45
00:04:42,540 --> 00:04:44,050
I didn't even ask for her name.

46
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,290
Cover your ears.

47
00:04:58,330 --> 00:04:59,390
I'll get you out in no time.

48
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:18,810
[Murderer.]

49
00:05:43,270 --> 00:05:44,310
Let me see.

50
00:05:45,409 --> 00:05:46,470
You don't have a fever.

51
00:05:46,909 --> 00:05:48,909
Do you feel sick or uncomfortable?

52
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,610
No.

53
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:52,710
Shall we take a day off from school?

54
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:54,520
No, I'm fine.

55
00:05:54,580 --> 00:05:55,680
I want to go to school.

56
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:57,350
Are you sure?

57
00:05:57,650 --> 00:05:59,120
You don't have to push yourself.

58
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,660
Okay then.
Let's eat breakfast and go to school.

59
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,960
Here. Look.

60
00:06:10,060 --> 00:06:11,270
I burnt it!

61
00:06:12,530 --> 00:06:13,800
I don't want to eat that.

62
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:16,740
It still tastes good.

63
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:19,940
Yi-chan,

64
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:24,680
did you see anyone
before going into the locker yesterday?

65
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:31,520
I don't know.

66
00:06:31,820 --> 00:06:32,890
I didn't see anyone.

67
00:06:33,690 --> 00:06:36,620
Okay, it's fine. Eat your breakfast.

68
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:46,830
[Yesterday, a kid was trapped in a locker
during the reception event.]

69
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:46,900
[HSC Mom Group chat]

70
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,300
[My gosh! I got goosebumps
just by hearing that.]

71
00:06:50,370 --> 00:06:51,440
[Which kid from which class?]

72
00:06:51,510 --> 00:06:53,010
[Which kid from which class?]

73
00:06:58,380 --> 00:06:59,580
[Oh, that mom.]

74
00:06:59,909 --> 00:07:01,480
[-Yesterday...
-Hush.]

75
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,390
Cheer up, Yi-chan. Okay?

76
00:07:09,460 --> 00:07:10,530
Have a good day.

77
00:07:17,570 --> 00:07:20,200
[Anyway, how did that kind of kid
enter this school?]

78
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,540
[Seriously.]

79
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:14,820
Oh, no.

80
00:09:58,460 --> 00:09:59,490
Whatever.

81
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:07,740
One of my alums in South Africa
sent me this rooibos tea.

82
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:09,500
I see.

83
00:10:11,140 --> 00:10:13,510
I can't imagine how surprised

84
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:15,410
and worried you were.

85
00:10:15,580 --> 00:10:18,250
Anyway, it's a relief that the child

86
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:19,750
didn't get hurt.

87
00:10:19,950 --> 00:10:22,280
Did you check the CCTV of the incident?

88
00:10:22,350 --> 00:10:24,120
Upon checking, that area

89
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:26,790
was a blind spot behind the pillar.

90
00:10:27,090 --> 00:10:28,290
A blind spot?

91
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:31,960
We will pay more attention to
the kids' safety within the school.

92
00:10:32,660 --> 00:10:34,330
I'm sure you're worried,

93
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:37,600
but please let go of your anger, and--

94
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:40,900
Mr. Han, this isn't an issue of me
letting go of my anger.

95
00:10:41,270 --> 00:10:44,070
What will happen if an accident
like this were to happen again?

96
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:46,910
Or what if someone did that on purpose?

97
00:10:46,970 --> 00:10:49,080
No way, it can't be on purpose.

98
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:50,380
How could that...

99
00:10:51,210 --> 00:10:53,750
That could never happen.

100
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:57,520
This is just an accident that happened

101
00:10:57,590 --> 00:10:58,750
while the kids were playing.

102
00:10:58,820 --> 00:11:00,690
How can you be so sure?

103
00:11:01,290 --> 00:11:03,720
A child was trapped in a CCTV blind spot.

104
00:11:03,790 --> 00:11:05,930
There was suspicious graffiti
on the window.

105
00:11:06,190 --> 00:11:08,700
It's too much to say that
this is all a coincidence.

106
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:11,400
Aren't you being
too optimistic about all this?

107
00:11:13,170 --> 00:11:14,170
Well...

108
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:18,070
I completely understand how you feel.

109
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:21,780
But don't be too agitated.

110
00:11:22,510 --> 00:11:26,310
Could you please trust the school
and follow along?

111
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,820
May I see the CCTV footage?

112
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:33,390
The hallway of the locker room
on the first floor is cornered.

113
00:11:33,450 --> 00:11:36,490
Because of the camera angle,
this is the only footage we have.

114
00:11:38,060 --> 00:11:39,160
I see.

115
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:43,100
Were your suspicions cleared up?

116
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,700
Yes, well but...

117
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:52,810
I can't imagine how surprised and worried
you were.

118
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:58,310
I apologize for the late greetings.

119
00:11:58,450 --> 00:12:00,180
I'm Doh Jin-sol,
the chairman of the board.

120
00:12:00,510 --> 00:12:01,580
Yes.

121
00:12:02,180 --> 00:12:06,420
As the chairman,
I'm so sorry that this incident happened.

122
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:07,720
I'm sorry.

123
00:12:07,860 --> 00:12:09,120
Oh, yes.

124
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:14,600
I've ordered additional CCTVs
to be installed for the blind spot.

125
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:17,670
We will make sure something like this
never happens again.

126
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:19,500
We'll be thoroughly careful.

127
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:24,510
And if you want to check all the CCTVs,

128
00:12:24,810 --> 00:12:28,140
we have to go through some procedures.

129
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:32,610
Yes, the data file is too large.

130
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:34,120
It will take some time.

131
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:37,650
According to school security regulations,
we have some procedures too.

132
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:39,120
It's all right for now.

133
00:12:40,020 --> 00:12:42,790
More than that, there's something

134
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:44,860
I wanted to ask you.

135
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:10,450
-I'm sorry.
-No worries.

136
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,860
My husband is related
to the school's foundation?

137
00:13:18,660 --> 00:13:23,600
CEO An not only had a special relationship
with our foundation,

138
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:27,230
but he also sent
his full interest and support.

139
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:31,510
I'm sincerely sorry for CEO An.

140
00:13:31,610 --> 00:13:33,770
I'm sorry for your loss.

141
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:37,650
Then what about the invitation?

142
00:13:37,850 --> 00:13:39,350
I sent it.

143
00:13:39,580 --> 00:13:42,150
It was CEO An's wish too.

144
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:45,620
I'm sorry I didn't inform you
enough in advance.

145
00:13:45,890 --> 00:13:48,420
Don't be. I should be thanking you.

146
00:13:48,860 --> 00:13:52,130
I don't know the details of what happened

147
00:13:52,190 --> 00:13:54,360
to Yi-chan at his previous school,

148
00:13:54,630 --> 00:13:57,330
but it seems you went through a lot.

149
00:13:57,400 --> 00:14:00,230
It was my son
who went through more than I did.

150
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:05,370
I watched Yi-chan
during the class participation evaluation.

151
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:07,710
Number 35.

152
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:11,250
Yi-chan An, will you share your thoughts?

153
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:16,550
I want to be happier with my mom.

154
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:18,420
I want to see her smile.

155
00:14:18,490 --> 00:14:21,290
It's a nice reason. Good job.

156
00:14:21,990 --> 00:14:23,290
[Yi-chan said that?]

157
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:26,460
Yi-chan is a student full of potential,

158
00:14:26,530 --> 00:14:29,100
just what our school is looking for.

159
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:31,170
Of course, he might be different
in some ways

160
00:14:31,230 --> 00:14:34,400
from the other students in this school.

161
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Thank you
for seeing the good sides of him.

162
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:40,210
He really wanted to come to this school.

163
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:45,280
It seems there are some rumors
about Yi-chan's admission.

164
00:14:45,350 --> 00:14:48,280
Was he given any special treatment?

165
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:49,950
Well...

166
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:53,850
As I mentioned earlier,

167
00:14:54,390 --> 00:14:57,860
your husband, CEO An, was deeply involved

168
00:14:57,930 --> 00:15:01,500
in the establishing, donating,
and investing of our foundation.

169
00:15:01,930 --> 00:15:04,930
How deeply, to be exact?

170
00:15:06,830 --> 00:15:08,070
Well...

171
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:13,640
To the point where Yi-chan was
the first on the acceptance list.

172
00:15:14,210 --> 00:15:16,310
How about that?

173
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:18,050
Do you mean Yi-chan...

174
00:15:18,110 --> 00:15:21,480
Of course,
it's not just because of CEO An.

175
00:15:21,780 --> 00:15:24,220
Yi-chan is no doubt a great student

176
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:26,590
that our school is looking for.

177
00:15:27,660 --> 00:15:30,590
I'll make sure your expectations
in choosing our school

178
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:34,530
are met to the fullest degree.

179
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,730
Trust me.

180
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:38,300
I swear on my title
as the chairman of the board.

181
00:15:39,570 --> 00:15:40,970
Thank you.

182
00:15:54,780 --> 00:15:55,980
Hello?

183
00:15:56,950 --> 00:15:58,590
Yes, that's me.

184
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:01,220
Yes, I'll be right there.

185
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,290
There was an English level test

186
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,960
for the students
in the admissions evaluation.

187
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:11,270
For Class B of Grade One,

188
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:14,440
the average accelerated reading score
was 1.8

189
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:16,300
[Evaluation criteria according to
the level of difficulty of English books]

190
00:16:14,570 --> 00:16:18,040
while Yi-chan was 1.0.

191
00:16:18,470 --> 00:16:20,070
That means...

192
00:16:20,140 --> 00:16:22,810
He's below the class average.

193
00:16:23,610 --> 00:16:27,510
Of course,
he's adjusting well to the classes

194
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:30,850
but supplementary lessons seem necessary.

195
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:33,890
Right, I get what you're saying.

196
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:36,760
I'll think about what to do.

197
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:38,830
How about asking the other mothers

198
00:16:38,890 --> 00:16:41,500
for advice in the group chat?

199
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:44,130
A group chat? Is there a class group chat?

200
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,570
I'm sure the mothers shared

201
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:49,440
their numbers after last night's event.
Didn't you get any message?

202
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,310
Not yet.

203
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:52,770
Then...

204
00:16:53,270 --> 00:16:56,540
You'll be able to get help
from your buddy mom.

205
00:16:56,610 --> 00:16:58,780
It's a system where students
who moved up from kindergarten

206
00:16:58,850 --> 00:17:02,550
are matched with new students so that
they can help adjust well to the school.

207
00:17:02,850 --> 00:17:06,190
As for Yi-chan... Let's see.

208
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:08,960
-It's Hwang Jae-in.
-I see.

209
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:11,890
-She'll soon get in touch.
-Thank you.

210
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:34,080
Oh, my.

211
00:17:38,790 --> 00:17:39,990
My gosh!

212
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:56,040
Gosh. Are you all right?

213
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:57,970
Yes.

214
00:17:58,710 --> 00:18:00,010
Use this.

215
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:02,980
-No, I'm fine.
-But you're soaked.

216
00:18:04,710 --> 00:18:06,710
It'll dry quickly with the breeze.

217
00:18:07,110 --> 00:18:09,080
You're definitely going to catch a cold.

218
00:18:10,620 --> 00:18:13,050
Use it or not, it's up to you.

219
00:18:13,790 --> 00:18:16,360
But don't treat me like a weirdo.

220
00:19:51,350 --> 00:19:52,990
I'm here to give this back to you.

221
00:19:53,590 --> 00:19:55,660
It was useful. Thank you.

222
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:59,690
Well, it's just something
I picked up off the ground.

223
00:20:11,070 --> 00:20:13,110
Wait. Do you know how to surf?

224
00:20:13,870 --> 00:20:17,140
No. It just looks dangerous.

225
00:20:17,210 --> 00:20:19,150
And a bit reckless.

226
00:20:20,180 --> 00:20:22,420
My gosh, you're judging it
by how it looks.

227
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:24,720
You wouldn't know unless you try it.

228
00:20:24,990 --> 00:20:26,850
And don't people usually

229
00:20:27,090 --> 00:20:30,960
have an itch
for dangerous and reckless things?

230
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:35,060
Well, I don't have an itch for those.

231
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:39,000
-Well then.
-Right.

232
00:20:58,520 --> 00:21:01,120
[Hello, Yi-chan's mom.
I'm Jae-in's mom, your buddy mom.]

233
00:21:01,190 --> 00:21:02,760
It's here.

234
00:21:03,890 --> 00:21:05,860
[Hello. Nice to meet you!]

235
00:21:05,930 --> 00:21:08,430
[I actually have a lot to ask.]

236
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:10,360
[Hello, Yi-chan's mom.
I'm Jae-in's mom and your buddy mom.]

237
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:19,470
[Hello. Nice to meet you!
I actually have a lot to ask.]

238
00:21:18,470 --> 00:21:21,410
[I don't think
I'm in the class group chat.]

239
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,480
[Can you add me to the chat?]

240
00:21:23,340 --> 00:21:24,910
[I don't think I'm in the class
group chat. Can you add me to the chat?]

241
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,150
[Welcome.]

242
00:21:33,490 --> 00:21:34,590
[Welcome.]

243
00:21:46,130 --> 00:21:47,500
-It's difficult.
-You're doing great.

244
00:21:47,570 --> 00:21:50,040
-Good.
-Pull your chin down.

245
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:52,940
-Stop rocking your body.
-Great.

246
00:21:53,010 --> 00:21:54,240
Keep your posture.

247
00:21:55,410 --> 00:21:57,510
It's unbelievable to the point
I can't even laugh about it.

248
00:21:57,980 --> 00:22:00,180
Ji-seon, this isn't right.

249
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:02,850
How can we let a kid like him
and our kids...

250
00:22:08,090 --> 00:22:10,260
[HSC International School]

251
00:22:10,390 --> 00:22:12,830
[Hello. Sorry for my late greeting.]

252
00:22:12,890 --> 00:22:14,060
[I'm Yi-chan's mom.]

253
00:22:14,130 --> 00:22:16,160
[I must have been left out
of the group chat.]

254
00:22:16,960 --> 00:22:19,670
Oh, my gosh.
How did she join this chat room?

255
00:22:21,170 --> 00:22:23,740
Don't be too sensitive.

256
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:26,410
Ji-seon, because of this woman,
my Si-woo...

257
00:22:27,670 --> 00:22:29,910
I hated her from the moment we met.

258
00:22:29,980 --> 00:22:31,710
When I hate people, I hate them to death.

259
00:22:31,780 --> 00:22:33,010
You know how I am.

260
00:22:35,180 --> 00:22:37,750
She won't be able
to hold out here for long.

261
00:22:37,820 --> 00:22:39,720
She'll soon realize it too.

262
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:44,990
[Nice to meet you Yi-chan's mom.]

263
00:22:45,490 --> 00:22:47,490
[We must've missed you yesterday.]

264
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:54,070
That reminds me, did your husband
come to my hotel Monday night?

265
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,140
-What?
-I caught a glimpse

266
00:22:58,470 --> 00:23:01,040
and the man getting on the lobby elevator
looked like your husband.

267
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:04,080
You must've mistaken him for someone else.

268
00:23:04,140 --> 00:23:06,710
He came home yesterday
from a business trip to Europe.

269
00:23:06,780 --> 00:23:08,650
You know his looks are plain.

270
00:23:10,250 --> 00:23:12,520
Even if it's because of work,

271
00:23:13,050 --> 00:23:14,690
don't leave him alone too much

272
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:16,320
so that nothing troublesome happens.

273
00:23:16,390 --> 00:23:18,630
Gosh, stop it.

274
00:23:18,790 --> 00:23:21,730
He's on a business trip
for more than half of the year.

275
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:23,960
Men will use any means

276
00:23:24,030 --> 00:23:26,700
to cheat if they decide to.

277
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:31,000
But you shouldn't leave
any room for him to cheat.

278
00:23:31,740 --> 00:23:33,570
He can cheat if he wants to.

279
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:35,480
I'm Cha Do-yeong.

280
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:36,810
If someone were to cheat,

281
00:23:37,580 --> 00:23:38,910
it'll be me who cheats on him first.

282
00:25:20,850 --> 00:25:21,950
[Wrong PIN]

283
00:25:26,490 --> 00:25:27,950
[Hint]

284
00:25:37,900 --> 00:25:39,600
Yi-chan, what are you doing?

285
00:25:42,370 --> 00:25:46,370
I'm drawing a picture of my family
to show in class.

286
00:25:46,810 --> 00:25:47,940
Really?

287
00:25:50,210 --> 00:25:53,050
Mom, is it okay to draw Dad?

288
00:25:53,810 --> 00:25:56,980
Of course, if you want to.

289
00:25:57,080 --> 00:25:58,950
You once told me this.

290
00:25:59,120 --> 00:26:02,120
Just because we can't see Dad
doesn't mean he's gone.

291
00:26:02,660 --> 00:26:05,730
That's right. He's not gone

292
00:26:05,830 --> 00:26:06,990
as long as we remember him.

293
00:26:07,130 --> 00:26:09,460
Does that mean he's with us?

294
00:26:12,770 --> 00:26:14,500
I believe so.

295
00:26:25,350 --> 00:26:27,610
-Daddy should go here.
-Yi-chan.

296
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:29,020
Did you make any friends yet?

297
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:31,790
What should we do tomorrow?

298
00:26:33,020 --> 00:26:37,090
Mom, is it okay if I play
with the other kids after school?

299
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:40,490
Well, do you want to do that?

300
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:42,060
What do you want to do?

301
00:26:43,730 --> 00:26:46,800
I want to play Catch the Dragon's Tail
and play with water guns.

302
00:26:46,870 --> 00:26:49,600
What else? I want to go fishing too.

303
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:54,370
Then should we ask the other kids?

304
00:26:54,440 --> 00:26:56,780
Can we do that? So exciting!

305
00:27:03,520 --> 00:27:04,750
[It's Yi-chan's mom.]

306
00:27:05,220 --> 00:27:08,290
[Can any of the kids play with Yi-chan
after school tomorrow?]

307
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:10,120
[Can any of the kids play with Yi-chan
after school tomorrow?]

308
00:27:10,620 --> 00:27:12,960
The skin is turning gray.

309
00:27:13,060 --> 00:27:15,330
[Can any of the kids play with Yi-chan
after school tomorrow?]

310
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:16,000
I'm sure at least one of them

311
00:27:16,930 --> 00:27:18,200
will reply.

312
00:27:19,030 --> 00:27:21,130
[My kid has other plans.]

313
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:23,570
[Too bad. We have plans too.]

314
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:25,210
[Sorry, but we can't.]

315
00:27:34,410 --> 00:27:35,420
Hey.

316
00:27:36,950 --> 00:27:40,020
Of course. A minivan will pick us up
in front of the school.

317
00:27:40,220 --> 00:27:42,090
Just be there on time.

318
00:27:43,020 --> 00:27:46,390
We could go for a round of golf
while the kids play.

319
00:27:49,900 --> 00:27:50,960
That kid's mom?

320
00:27:51,770 --> 00:27:53,200
I'm sure she'll figure something out.

321
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:56,000
Okay. See you tomorrow.

322
00:28:00,410 --> 00:28:03,040
Ms. Nam, the lesson is over.

323
00:28:03,740 --> 00:28:05,680
How did Jun-hee do?

324
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:07,350
Did she keep up?

325
00:28:07,550 --> 00:28:08,550
Yes.

326
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:12,490
She's excellent. Such a brilliant kid.

327
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:14,350
Please teach her a lot.

328
00:28:14,990 --> 00:28:18,830
Also, to the other kids...
You know, right?

329
00:28:19,230 --> 00:28:20,560
Yes, of course.

330
00:28:20,890 --> 00:28:22,400
Between ourselves.

331
00:28:25,730 --> 00:28:27,230
I'm home.

332
00:28:27,300 --> 00:28:29,500
You're home late. Say hello.

333
00:28:29,900 --> 00:28:33,970
This is Jun-hee's English tutor,
Ms. Rachel Cho.

334
00:28:34,370 --> 00:28:35,580
Nice to meet you.

335
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:36,840
Oh, I see.

336
00:28:37,410 --> 00:28:40,050
Please teach Jun-hee well.

337
00:28:42,780 --> 00:28:45,190
I'll be going then, Ms. Nam.

338
00:28:46,020 --> 00:28:47,050
Okay.

339
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:58,100
-Did you have a drink?
-Well, yes.

340
00:28:58,600 --> 00:29:01,800
I grabbed a drink with my colleagues
at a food stall in front of the clinic

341
00:29:01,940 --> 00:29:03,370
after work.

342
00:29:03,500 --> 00:29:05,310
Why a food stall?

343
00:29:08,310 --> 00:29:11,340
For old times' sake.

344
00:29:12,050 --> 00:29:15,150
Do you remember when we first met?

345
00:29:15,220 --> 00:29:16,580
The food stall tteokbokki that we had.

346
00:29:17,650 --> 00:29:20,590
You said you'd never tried soondae before.

347
00:29:22,220 --> 00:29:24,890
I suddenly remembered it,
so I bought some for you.

348
00:29:27,860 --> 00:29:29,730
You were gorgeous back then.

349
00:29:34,330 --> 00:29:35,540
You're drunk.

350
00:29:35,840 --> 00:29:37,240
Go upstairs and rest.

351
00:29:37,670 --> 00:29:39,910
You're flying to Seoul
first thing in the morning.

352
00:29:40,210 --> 00:29:41,340
All right.

353
00:29:53,290 --> 00:29:56,690
Ma'am, please ventilate
the kitchen and the living room.

354
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:06,570
Let's hurry.

355
00:30:13,710 --> 00:30:14,910
Oh, good morning.

356
00:30:15,010 --> 00:30:16,980
-Are you going golfing?
-Yes.

357
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:19,210
I'm playing a round this afternoon.

358
00:30:19,580 --> 00:30:21,110
Join me sometime.

359
00:30:21,650 --> 00:30:23,680
My hotel has a pretty nice golf course.

360
00:30:23,750 --> 00:30:25,720
I don't play golf.

361
00:30:25,820 --> 00:30:28,050
-It doesn't really interest me.
-Really?

362
00:30:30,090 --> 00:30:33,060
But there's nothing else to do
around here.

363
00:30:34,890 --> 00:30:37,100
-See you around.
-See you.

364
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,840
Mom, don't you have any friends here yet?

365
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:47,340
Well, I'll probably make some soon,
like you did.

366
00:30:47,410 --> 00:30:49,210
You should try harder.

367
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:51,280
It's not fun playing alone.

368
00:30:51,950 --> 00:30:54,180
Okay. I'll try harder.

369
00:30:57,150 --> 00:30:58,890
[Here are the keys to your house.]

370
00:30:59,150 --> 00:31:01,390
Here's the key card
to the shared facilities.

371
00:31:01,690 --> 00:31:03,860
You can find more information
in these brochures.

372
00:31:04,520 --> 00:31:06,090
Please give them a read.

373
00:31:06,490 --> 00:31:09,630
Your terrace and the shared facilities

374
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:12,200
will be cleaned by our staff.

375
00:31:12,270 --> 00:31:13,300
I see.

376
00:31:13,370 --> 00:31:16,070
You've been here before, right?

377
00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:19,440
No. My husband came here alone
to sign the contract.

378
00:31:19,910 --> 00:31:22,340
Can I get the keys to Building F?

379
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:23,880
The people went out.

380
00:31:23,940 --> 00:31:25,650
Sure, one second.

381
00:31:26,050 --> 00:31:29,880
Why would you drag your kid
all the way to this island?

382
00:31:30,650 --> 00:31:33,550
-Pardon?
-The development is a good thing.

383
00:31:33,650 --> 00:31:37,420
These days, horses are sent to Seoul,
and people are sent to Jeju Island.

384
00:31:37,590 --> 00:31:39,690
-Am I right?
-Yes.

385
00:31:39,890 --> 00:31:41,230
I'll be going now.

386
00:31:41,290 --> 00:31:43,830
-Thank you for your help.
-Sure. See you.

387
00:31:48,270 --> 00:31:49,670
Why would you say that?

388
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:51,440
She's moving into the house

389
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:54,270
-I told you about the other day.
-So what?

390
00:31:55,070 --> 00:31:57,210
Isn't she the one who came here
with the man who died?

391
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:00,480
I can't really tell.

392
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:05,820
The owner didn't add
any emergency contacts.

393
00:32:06,690 --> 00:32:09,720
Then is there no way
to find out the number?

394
00:32:09,790 --> 00:32:11,720
Either someone has to call this number

395
00:32:11,790 --> 00:32:13,730
or the phone has to be unlocked.

396
00:32:13,930 --> 00:32:16,260
Can't you reach the owner of the phone?

397
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:17,460
No.

398
00:32:27,910 --> 00:32:30,110
Let's go play in the sea.

399
00:32:34,410 --> 00:32:36,620
-Will there be fish there?
-Of course.

400
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:39,890
We'll catch fish and shellfish
and everything, okay?

401
00:33:14,650 --> 00:33:18,290
Excuse me. My kid and I
are thinking of playing on the beach.

402
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:21,390
Oh my.

403
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:22,830
We meet again.

404
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:25,670
Do you own this place?

405
00:33:27,900 --> 00:33:30,300
You want to play on the beach?

406
00:33:34,140 --> 00:33:36,410
-Do you have some muscles?
-What?

407
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:39,180
If you do, canoes aren't bad.

408
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:41,650
But snorkeling is the easiest with a kid.

409
00:33:42,780 --> 00:33:44,650
This is for kids...

410
00:33:47,150 --> 00:33:48,320
But it'll fit.

411
00:33:51,790 --> 00:33:52,890
Here.

412
00:33:55,860 --> 00:33:58,900
You said you weren't into surfing,
but does that look doable?

413
00:33:59,100 --> 00:34:00,530
Right.

414
00:34:01,130 --> 00:34:03,300
So, are you done picking stuff out?

415
00:34:03,370 --> 00:34:05,840
I'm good but you have a new customer.

416
00:34:07,510 --> 00:34:10,510
-You're not the owner?
-I'm a customer too.

417
00:34:10,710 --> 00:34:13,010
He's an employee and the owner...

418
00:34:13,080 --> 00:34:15,420
There should be a cat.
I guess it went out.

419
00:34:18,580 --> 00:34:20,989
-Call me when my orders arrive.
-All right. Bye.

420
00:34:24,590 --> 00:34:26,230
What's with him?

421
00:34:27,690 --> 00:34:28,900
Thank you!

422
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:30,699
-Get home safely.
-Okay.

423
00:34:36,370 --> 00:34:37,469
Oh, my.

424
00:34:37,870 --> 00:34:39,310
Move.

425
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:41,840
-Come on.
-Oh, my gosh.

426
00:34:42,110 --> 00:34:43,340
Gosh.

427
00:34:50,719 --> 00:34:52,590
[-Too bad. We have plans too.
-Sorry, but we can't.]

428
00:34:53,820 --> 00:34:57,060
What do I do? Everyone's busy.

429
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:05,630
Hey, Yi-chan!

430
00:35:07,070 --> 00:35:08,370
Yi-chan!

431
00:35:10,770 --> 00:35:12,170
How was school?

432
00:35:12,510 --> 00:35:18,010
Yi-chan, I'm sorry but all your friends
seem to be busy today.

433
00:35:18,080 --> 00:35:19,750
So how about we go to the beach instead?

434
00:35:19,810 --> 00:35:21,680
Look, I...

435
00:35:22,620 --> 00:35:24,680
I don't want to. I just want to go home.

436
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:29,660
Why? Did something happen?

437
00:35:30,860 --> 00:35:31,860
What is it?

438
00:35:34,230 --> 00:35:37,600
Hey, Jun-hee. We can have mango bingsu
if we go to your hotel today, right?

439
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:40,830
Hey, her hotel's food is the best.

440
00:35:40,900 --> 00:35:42,970
I want 2, no 3 dishes.

441
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:45,610
Sure. Eat up, you pigs.

442
00:35:46,070 --> 00:35:48,880
Instead, we have to play
Catch the Dragon's Tail in the pool.

443
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:52,780
I'm not going to play any other games.
Okay?

444
00:35:52,950 --> 00:35:54,650
-Okay.
-Let's play something else.

445
00:35:54,710 --> 00:35:57,120
-I don't want to.
-Guys. Where are you going?

446
00:35:57,180 --> 00:35:59,720
Jun-hee invited us to her hotel.

447
00:36:00,620 --> 00:36:02,590
Guys, what are you doing? Hurry up!

448
00:36:02,660 --> 00:36:05,460
-Mom!
-Mom!

449
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:09,900
-Mom!
-Goodness!

450
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:11,530
-Mom!
-Mom!

451
00:36:11,900 --> 00:36:14,170
Why did you say anything?

452
00:36:19,870 --> 00:36:23,680
My gosh. They're so mean.

453
00:36:24,110 --> 00:36:27,310
Yi-chan, we can have
more fun than them on our own.

454
00:36:27,380 --> 00:36:29,920
Let's go snorkeling and ride the canoe...

455
00:36:29,980 --> 00:36:33,350
No! I want to play with my friends,
not you.

456
00:36:37,060 --> 00:36:38,690
All right.

457
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:44,760
[Jae-in's Mom]

458
00:36:41,190 --> 00:36:42,960
[It's your buddy mom, Jae-in's mom.]

459
00:36:43,030 --> 00:36:44,900
[We'd like to play with Yi-chan today.]

460
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:47,470
Yi-chan! Great news.

461
00:36:47,530 --> 00:36:49,240
Jae-in can play with you.

462
00:36:49,300 --> 00:36:52,140
-Jae-in?
-Yes. Great, right?

463
00:36:52,410 --> 00:36:53,640
Are you close with her?

464
00:36:54,710 --> 00:36:56,410
An Yi-chan!

465
00:36:59,380 --> 00:37:01,610
-Hi.
-Hello.

466
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:04,980
Oh, my. Hello!

467
00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:08,960
Thank you so much for the other day.

468
00:37:09,090 --> 00:37:12,390
I couldn't get your name
and it kept bothering me.

469
00:37:12,690 --> 00:37:15,660
Don't mention it.
Things were so hectic that day.

470
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:19,070
Is Yi-chan feeling better?

471
00:37:19,770 --> 00:37:21,300
Yes, thankfully.

472
00:37:21,370 --> 00:37:23,600
I was worried
because he was really shocked.

473
00:37:25,370 --> 00:37:28,110
-Hi, Yi-chan.
-Hello.

474
00:37:28,170 --> 00:37:30,080
Mom, she's Jae-in.

475
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:32,380
Jae-in?

476
00:37:33,350 --> 00:37:34,610
By Jae-in...

477
00:37:35,150 --> 00:37:36,850
Oh, my! Are you my buddy mom?

478
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:38,990
My goodness.

479
00:37:39,690 --> 00:37:42,590
This is great.
I'm really glad to meet you.

480
00:37:42,790 --> 00:37:45,160
-Please take good care of me.
-Likewise.

481
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:54,030
Anyway, she's going to be busy
if her son wants to catch up.

482
00:37:54,100 --> 00:37:56,340
I'm sure she'll do well on her own.

483
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:59,570
The mom is a lawyer so she must be smart.

484
00:38:00,440 --> 00:38:02,940
She's surely not your average person.

485
00:38:03,040 --> 00:38:04,640
She was on the Internet's
top trending list

486
00:38:04,710 --> 00:38:07,110
and her face was all over the news.

487
00:38:08,510 --> 00:38:10,080
Oh, my gosh. She's heading this way.

488
00:38:12,420 --> 00:38:13,650
Hello.

489
00:38:15,420 --> 00:38:17,020
Welcome, Yi-chan's mom.

490
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:21,090
It seems there's a gathering today.
But I guess we weren't invited?

491
00:38:25,130 --> 00:38:27,430
Jun-hee is really shy.

492
00:38:27,700 --> 00:38:30,570
It seems she's not close with Yi-chan yet.

493
00:38:31,370 --> 00:38:33,340
You understand, right? They're kids.

494
00:38:33,910 --> 00:38:35,880
Of course. There's no way

495
00:38:35,940 --> 00:38:38,080
you would've done that intentionally.

496
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:40,750
But we have plans too.

497
00:38:42,250 --> 00:38:46,290
Then why don't you go on your way?

498
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:55,660
Thank you for inviting me,
but what a shame.

499
00:38:56,230 --> 00:38:58,800
Jae-in made promises with Yi-chan first.

500
00:39:00,330 --> 00:39:01,500
I see.

501
00:39:07,510 --> 00:39:11,240
Have a wonderful time
and please invite us next time.

502
00:39:14,250 --> 00:39:16,620
-Let's go, Yi-chan!
-Jae-in!

503
00:39:47,650 --> 00:39:50,220
Wasn't I right?
She's not your average person.

504
00:39:50,380 --> 00:39:53,120
She kept a straight face.

505
00:39:53,690 --> 00:39:54,950
Right, Ji-seon?

506
00:39:55,020 --> 00:39:58,620
Just ignore her.
It's not as if she'll hang out with us.

507
00:39:59,090 --> 00:40:01,690
But why did Jae-in's mom choose her?

508
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:04,900
Who's Jae-in's mom?
I've never heard of her before.

509
00:40:04,960 --> 00:40:07,900
She's a returnee who came back
from Hong Kong six months ago.

510
00:40:08,330 --> 00:40:11,670
It sounded like
she lived there for a while.

511
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:14,370
I don't know what she does,

512
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:17,010
but she has a gallery down south.

513
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:18,610
Her husband's job is a mystery too

514
00:40:18,680 --> 00:40:21,380
but such a young woman
is busy all by herself.

515
00:40:21,450 --> 00:40:23,850
Now I remember that mom!

516
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:26,190
I heard people talk about a pretty woman

517
00:40:26,250 --> 00:40:29,190
living alone with her kid
when I went to work out.

518
00:40:29,260 --> 00:40:30,790
They said she's divorced or something.

519
00:40:31,220 --> 00:40:34,690
But seriously, why'd she choose her?
We even invited her.

520
00:40:34,790 --> 00:40:37,300
Stop with the idle talk

521
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:39,030
and focus on our business.

522
00:40:47,740 --> 00:40:50,280
-Nice shot, Ji-seon!
-Nice shot!

523
00:40:50,340 --> 00:40:53,180
You played every day
and now you're practically a pro!

524
00:40:53,980 --> 00:40:55,710
You should work hard to keep up with us.

525
00:40:55,780 --> 00:40:57,450
If not, you can't join us.

526
00:40:57,950 --> 00:41:00,520
I've never been good at sports.

527
00:41:00,590 --> 00:41:03,320
I came to take photos today.

528
00:41:04,090 --> 00:41:05,990
I'm not just talking about sports.

529
00:41:06,230 --> 00:41:08,790
Isn't that a mesh bag to carry mandarins?

530
00:41:08,990 --> 00:41:10,600
Sorry.

531
00:41:11,030 --> 00:41:13,830
You'll be banned from my country club
if you come looking like this again.

532
00:41:14,770 --> 00:41:18,400
Gosh. You all have no clue
what fashion is.

533
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:20,670
Take photos for me. Okay?

534
00:41:20,740 --> 00:41:23,680
Too much is as bad as too little.
You always overdo everything.

535
00:41:30,120 --> 00:41:31,550
I'm first.

536
00:41:31,980 --> 00:41:34,150
Wait for me, Yi-chan.

537
00:41:34,490 --> 00:41:37,290
-Hurry up.
-I'm trying.

538
00:41:39,990 --> 00:41:42,130
Oh, my. The kids are so good at this.

539
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:45,560
-The kids are so cute.
-This is so much fun.

540
00:41:45,830 --> 00:41:47,300
Let's go!

541
00:41:48,370 --> 00:41:51,070
Hey, Yi-chan. There's a lake next to us.

542
00:41:51,140 --> 00:41:53,370
-It really exists.
-I told you.

543
00:41:53,440 --> 00:41:54,570
-Right?
-Right.

544
00:41:55,140 --> 00:41:56,910
-Are you following us?
-Yes.

545
00:41:56,980 --> 00:41:59,210
-This is really fun.
-It is?

546
00:41:59,780 --> 00:42:01,250
Hurry up.

547
00:42:01,550 --> 00:42:02,920
Here I go!

548
00:42:06,150 --> 00:42:07,450
I'm exhausted.

549
00:42:07,750 --> 00:42:10,420
Really? Guys, come back
after you ride a bit more.

550
00:42:10,590 --> 00:42:11,720
Be careful!

551
00:42:14,790 --> 00:42:15,900
I'm tired.

552
00:42:21,170 --> 00:42:23,370
It's been a while since Yi-chan
had so much fun.

553
00:42:25,140 --> 00:42:27,110
Thank you for bringing us
to such a nice place.

554
00:42:27,170 --> 00:42:29,040
There's no need to be so stiff, Yeo-wool.

555
00:42:30,080 --> 00:42:31,880
I know, but still.

556
00:42:33,750 --> 00:42:37,120
Playing outside is better
than being inside a hotel.

557
00:42:37,180 --> 00:42:38,220
You're right.

558
00:42:38,650 --> 00:42:39,950
To be honest,

559
00:42:40,220 --> 00:42:43,090
I don't mesh well
with those moms and that kind of setting.

560
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:45,930
They talk too much,

561
00:42:45,990 --> 00:42:48,260
and I couldn't get used to

562
00:42:48,690 --> 00:42:50,430
hanging out together every day like that.

563
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:52,800
Me neither.

564
00:42:53,970 --> 00:42:56,900
And I certainly got on their bad side.

565
00:42:56,970 --> 00:42:59,940
They were so mean earlier
about the kids playing together.

566
00:43:01,270 --> 00:43:04,710
But thanks to that, we were able to come
to such a marvelous place.

567
00:43:06,350 --> 00:43:08,350
Something more marvelous
is waiting for you.

568
00:43:08,410 --> 00:43:09,880
Something more marvelous?

569
00:43:11,180 --> 00:43:14,220
-There!
-How did you do it?

570
00:43:14,990 --> 00:43:16,790
-Do you want to try it?
-Yes!

571
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:21,490
My gosh.

572
00:43:22,290 --> 00:43:23,900
-I almost caught it!
-Me too!

573
00:43:23,960 --> 00:43:25,400
They're having a blast.

574
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:29,840
When did you prepare all this?

575
00:43:29,900 --> 00:43:31,040
It looks good, right?

576
00:43:32,140 --> 00:43:34,870
-Oh, my. I got this.
-No.

577
00:43:34,940 --> 00:43:36,340
You should get some rest.

578
00:43:36,410 --> 00:43:38,610
No, I feel bad. Let me do it.

579
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:40,380
Let me try.

580
00:43:40,810 --> 00:43:42,080
Can I put this here?

581
00:43:42,250 --> 00:43:43,420
-Like this?
-Yes.

582
00:43:45,380 --> 00:43:47,520
-Hey!
-No, just let me do it.

583
00:43:47,690 --> 00:43:48,890
Hold on. Give me that.

584
00:43:57,630 --> 00:43:58,760
This is nice.

585
00:44:00,730 --> 00:44:02,940
I've never gone camping before.

586
00:44:04,700 --> 00:44:07,170
I should stick to you from now on.

587
00:44:09,710 --> 00:44:14,210
Right. What did you decide to do
about Yi-chan's English lessons?

588
00:44:15,410 --> 00:44:17,450
Oh, that. I don't know.

589
00:44:17,950 --> 00:44:20,050
Then how do you feel about
doing joint classes with Jae-in?

590
00:44:20,390 --> 00:44:23,060
She used to live in Hong Kong,
so her English is pretty good.

591
00:44:23,120 --> 00:44:25,120
If they study together,
it'll be helpful for Yi-chan.

592
00:44:25,190 --> 00:44:27,930
Are you sure? I'd love that,

593
00:44:27,990 --> 00:44:29,430
but Jae-in won't gain anything from it.

594
00:44:29,900 --> 00:44:32,800
What are you talking about?
It'll be good for her too.

595
00:44:33,530 --> 00:44:34,770
She made a friend.

596
00:44:40,110 --> 00:44:43,940
Right. The kids need friends
more than anything right now.

597
00:44:48,180 --> 00:44:51,350
My gosh, I completely lost track of time.

598
00:44:52,520 --> 00:44:53,750
Yi-chan.

599
00:44:54,490 --> 00:44:56,160
Let's go, Yi-chan.

600
00:44:56,890 --> 00:44:57,960
What time is it now?

601
00:45:11,840 --> 00:45:14,770
-You dropped this.
-Right, thanks.

602
00:45:15,970 --> 00:45:17,940
Gosh, it's getting late.

603
00:45:18,010 --> 00:45:19,010
We should get going.

604
00:45:19,080 --> 00:45:21,710
Next time, let's go somewhere nicer
without the kids.

605
00:45:21,850 --> 00:45:23,480
Yes, please.

606
00:45:26,620 --> 00:45:27,720
Come on, Yi-chan.

607
00:45:35,590 --> 00:45:38,260
My mom is Cha Do-yeong. She's a celebrity.

608
00:45:36,530 --> 00:45:38,100
[Korean, Introduce Your Family]

609
00:45:38,500 --> 00:45:41,500
And my dad is the CEO of Next Gate,
a gaming company.

610
00:45:41,770 --> 00:45:44,800
My dad is super busy developing games,

611
00:45:44,940 --> 00:45:47,010
so he's always away for work.

612
00:45:47,370 --> 00:45:49,610
[He left for another business trip today.]

613
00:45:50,240 --> 00:45:53,150
[He's never home anyway,
so it feels the same whether we're here]

614
00:45:53,510 --> 00:45:54,780
[or in Seoul.]

615
00:45:55,910 --> 00:45:57,320
Where are you going this time?

616
00:45:57,820 --> 00:46:00,050
-And for how long?
-What?

617
00:46:01,220 --> 00:46:04,560
Well, I'll be stopping by Shanghai first.

618
00:46:04,990 --> 00:46:08,560
Then I have to go to Singapore
and Hong Kong.

619
00:46:08,630 --> 00:46:10,130
I'll be away for at least a week.

620
00:46:11,660 --> 00:46:13,870
Sounds like you'll be touring
all of Southeast Asia.

621
00:46:15,030 --> 00:46:16,100
Is it really a business trip?

622
00:46:17,870 --> 00:46:20,270
What do you mean? That's so random.

623
00:46:21,640 --> 00:46:22,740
Well...

624
00:46:23,610 --> 00:46:25,880
Someone told me they saw you

625
00:46:26,150 --> 00:46:28,380
at the hotel here a few days ago,

626
00:46:28,780 --> 00:46:30,450
not in Europe.

627
00:46:38,090 --> 00:46:41,090
Why would I have been there?
That's absurd.

628
00:46:41,160 --> 00:46:42,760
Do you want to see my boarding pass?

629
00:46:43,230 --> 00:46:46,130
Oh, I took some photos.
Do you want to see them?

630
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:52,440
That's not necessary.

631
00:46:52,970 --> 00:46:56,010
I know you're not that dumb.

632
00:46:56,510 --> 00:46:59,140
You are free to do whatever you want.

633
00:46:59,310 --> 00:47:02,210
We agreed to respect each other's freedom
before we got married.

634
00:47:03,720 --> 00:47:06,550
Whatever you do, just don't get caught.

635
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:09,820
You know I hate being humiliated
more than anything else.

636
00:47:13,190 --> 00:47:15,660
Think whatever you want.

637
00:47:17,800 --> 00:47:21,300
Gosh, what a nice way
to send off your husband.

638
00:47:22,530 --> 00:47:23,600
Seriously...

639
00:47:24,340 --> 00:47:27,210
He brings me the latest game
from every business trip,

640
00:47:25,500 --> 00:47:31,610
[Korean, Introduce Your Family]

641
00:47:27,640 --> 00:47:29,110
so I love it.

642
00:47:29,340 --> 00:47:31,680
I hope he takes business trips
all the time.

643
00:47:31,880 --> 00:47:34,610
My mom also says
she prefers it when my dad is away.

644
00:47:34,850 --> 00:47:37,450
[Comforting reality shows
are the biggest trend right now.]

645
00:47:37,550 --> 00:47:40,850
[Devoted celebrity mom Cha Do-yeong
and her son's life in Jeju.]

646
00:47:40,990 --> 00:47:43,690
[I guarantee you. People will love it.]

647
00:47:43,790 --> 00:47:47,390
[Your son goes to an international school,
so it's perfect.]

648
00:47:47,460 --> 00:47:48,990
That is true, but...

649
00:47:49,530 --> 00:47:53,170
Anyway, I won't do it
unless I'm the main celebrity on the show.

650
00:47:53,270 --> 00:47:55,870
It's not just about me, you know.
It'll be Si-woo's TV debut.

651
00:47:56,840 --> 00:47:59,170
Okay, fine. Let's talk again later.

652
00:47:59,240 --> 00:48:00,770
[My mom has been taking some time off,]

653
00:48:00,840 --> 00:48:03,510
[but she's planning to start new dramas
and variety shows soon.]

654
00:48:04,080 --> 00:48:06,980
[So lately, she's been busy
talking with her agency]

655
00:48:07,180 --> 00:48:09,180
[and meeting people.]

656
00:48:09,250 --> 00:48:11,420
Mirror, mirror on the wall.

657
00:48:11,650 --> 00:48:13,150
Who is the prettiest...

658
00:48:14,350 --> 00:48:15,420
Oh, no!

659
00:48:15,590 --> 00:48:19,320
When did I get this? I can't believe it.

660
00:48:22,230 --> 00:48:23,260
No.

661
00:48:23,860 --> 00:48:26,430
There are plenty of apps for this.
I'll just edit it out.

662
00:48:38,680 --> 00:48:42,880
Mirror, mirror on the wall.
Who is the prettiest of them all?

663
00:48:40,850 --> 00:48:43,050
[New Post, No makeup]

664
00:48:44,820 --> 00:48:46,790
[Posting]

665
00:48:47,190 --> 00:48:49,390
That's it. Thank you!

666
00:48:52,620 --> 00:48:53,890
Well done.

667
00:48:54,690 --> 00:48:56,860
Who wants to go next?

668
00:48:57,630 --> 00:48:58,930
[Korean, Introduce Your Family]

669
00:48:58,030 --> 00:48:59,460
Yi-chan, do you want to go next?

670
00:49:02,500 --> 00:49:04,740
Let's give him a big hand.

671
00:49:11,740 --> 00:49:13,880
An Yi-chan, you don't have a dad.

672
00:49:13,950 --> 00:49:15,380
I have a dad.

673
00:49:16,050 --> 00:49:17,320
Liar.

674
00:49:17,480 --> 00:49:19,250
Your dad is dead.

675
00:49:19,320 --> 00:49:21,290
Why would you draw a dead person?

676
00:49:21,920 --> 00:49:24,160
That is not true. What do you even know?

677
00:49:24,220 --> 00:49:26,290
Ma'am, he's lying.

678
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:28,430
Liar. You can't even speak English.

679
00:49:28,560 --> 00:49:30,100
You stupid liar.

680
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:33,570
That's enough. Quiet.

681
00:49:33,630 --> 00:49:35,870
Both of you will get in trouble
if you don't stop.

682
00:49:36,670 --> 00:49:38,100
Yi-chan, you may continue.

683
00:49:42,470 --> 00:49:44,880
-My gosh.
-Go up. Go!

684
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:52,480
-Wow!
-Hey, can I try it?

685
00:49:52,550 --> 00:49:56,620
-I want to try it.
-Please? Just once.

686
00:49:57,020 --> 00:49:59,090
-Just once.
-Let me try it.

687
00:49:59,190 --> 00:50:02,630
-Let go. Hold on.
-Please, just once.

688
00:50:04,700 --> 00:50:07,700
-I said, no.
-Come on! You're mean.

689
00:50:09,230 --> 00:50:11,740
Hey, An Yi-chan.
Do you want to try it too?

690
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:14,910
Get lost, you stupid liar.

691
00:50:16,140 --> 00:50:19,510
-Hey, let me try it just once.
-No!

692
00:50:20,810 --> 00:50:22,880
Everyone, it's lunchtime.

693
00:50:22,950 --> 00:50:24,420
Let's move to the cafeteria.

694
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:26,350
-Yes, ma'am!
-Yes, ma'am!

695
00:50:28,820 --> 00:50:30,060
-Just once, okay?
-No.

696
00:50:30,120 --> 00:50:31,520
Just for a minute, okay?

697
00:50:31,590 --> 00:50:32,660
I said, no.

698
00:50:49,070 --> 00:50:51,380
-Enjoy.
-Thank you.

699
00:50:53,850 --> 00:50:56,050
-Enjoy.
-Thank you.

700
00:50:59,750 --> 00:51:01,990
-Enjoy.
-Thank you.

701
00:51:03,390 --> 00:51:05,120
Enjoy.

702
00:51:06,060 --> 00:51:07,790
Do you expect me to eat this?

703
00:51:12,300 --> 00:51:13,670
Egg.

704
00:51:15,270 --> 00:51:16,330
Hey, Kwak Si-woo.

705
00:51:17,540 --> 00:51:19,500
Can you actually eat this garbage?

706
00:51:19,640 --> 00:51:22,010
Yes. It's good. What's wrong with it?

707
00:51:22,070 --> 00:51:23,280
If you don't want it, I'll eat it.

708
00:51:23,340 --> 00:51:24,680
Give me your egg.

709
00:51:24,740 --> 00:51:28,410
Why don't we leave this
and take my car to a restaurant

710
00:51:28,480 --> 00:51:29,610
and eat something there instead?

711
00:51:30,350 --> 00:51:31,780
A restaurant?

712
00:51:32,580 --> 00:51:35,650
-Sounds great. Shall we?
-Let's go.

713
00:51:35,850 --> 00:51:38,490
Okay, very good. Let's go.

714
00:51:38,720 --> 00:51:39,790
It's on me.

715
00:51:40,260 --> 00:51:42,330
I can treat you. Let me.

716
00:52:18,830 --> 00:52:19,770
Wait.

717
00:52:23,670 --> 00:52:26,810
Hey, Yi-chan. Did you break it?

718
00:52:27,970 --> 00:52:31,140
An Yi-chan! Pay me back for my drone!

719
00:52:34,450 --> 00:52:36,350
Yi-chan broke it?

720
00:52:36,950 --> 00:52:40,450
I saw it on my way back from lunchtime.

721
00:52:40,520 --> 00:52:43,790
Yi-chan was standing
next to Si-woo's broken drone.

722
00:52:44,360 --> 00:52:46,930
Jun-hee, stay out of it.

723
00:52:48,560 --> 00:52:51,030
Pay me back! You have to!

724
00:52:51,100 --> 00:52:52,560
You broke my power drone!

725
00:52:52,660 --> 00:52:55,230
Si-woo, we get it. Be quiet now.

726
00:52:57,300 --> 00:53:01,370
Si-woo got it from his dad
when he entered this school.

727
00:53:01,670 --> 00:53:04,410
You don't have to pay us back,
but I do want a proper apology.

728
00:53:05,680 --> 00:53:09,310
Yi-chan, is it true?
It's okay, so please be honest.

729
00:53:09,380 --> 00:53:10,920
I won't scold you.

730
00:53:10,980 --> 00:53:13,050
All you have to do is
apologize for your mistake.

731
00:53:13,120 --> 00:53:14,720
Mom, I didn't break it.

732
00:53:14,790 --> 00:53:16,450
Stop lying!

733
00:53:16,660 --> 00:53:18,560
Everything you say is a lie!

734
00:53:18,620 --> 00:53:20,390
No, I really didn't do it.

735
00:53:23,400 --> 00:53:25,200
Yi-chan says he didn't do it.

736
00:53:25,260 --> 00:53:27,530
Maybe there was a misunderstanding.

737
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:29,030
A misunderstanding?

738
00:53:29,300 --> 00:53:32,040
Then I at least need to hear
an explanation.

739
00:53:32,100 --> 00:53:34,070
He was standing
right next to the broken drone.

740
00:53:34,140 --> 00:53:36,210
He must know what happened.

741
00:53:36,270 --> 00:53:38,480
Well, ladies.

742
00:53:38,540 --> 00:53:41,580
I didn't call you all here
so you could argue.

743
00:53:41,780 --> 00:53:43,480
The children are watching.

744
00:53:43,920 --> 00:53:45,420
Please calm down.

745
00:53:45,780 --> 00:53:47,650
Yi-chan, look at me.

746
00:53:48,820 --> 00:53:50,590
See? He can't say anything.

747
00:53:50,690 --> 00:53:51,920
Calm down.

748
00:53:52,960 --> 00:53:54,260
Gosh.

749
00:53:54,460 --> 00:53:57,730
I guess the rumors were right.

750
00:53:57,800 --> 00:53:59,160
I hear he has

751
00:53:59,230 --> 00:54:01,300
a record of school violence
from his previous school.

752
00:54:03,240 --> 00:54:05,770
Ms. Cha, please...

753
00:54:06,810 --> 00:54:08,640
You're out of line.

754
00:54:08,710 --> 00:54:11,080
-That has nothing to do with this.
-Whatever.

755
00:54:11,780 --> 00:54:14,350
Mr. Han, what are you going to do
about this?

756
00:54:14,410 --> 00:54:16,580
The kids only just started school.

757
00:54:16,650 --> 00:54:18,880
I don't want a kid like him
in my child's class.

758
00:54:18,950 --> 00:54:21,150
I feel the same way.

759
00:54:21,220 --> 00:54:23,890
The situation seems problematic.

760
00:54:34,170 --> 00:54:36,940
Ms. Hwang, hello. What brings you here?

761
00:54:37,400 --> 00:54:40,210
We're in the middle of discussing
something important here.

762
00:54:40,270 --> 00:54:43,880
I have something to tell you
regarding that matter.

763
00:54:44,910 --> 00:54:46,040
That drone...

764
00:54:47,450 --> 00:54:49,380
Yi-chan didn't do it.

765
00:55:30,690 --> 00:55:33,260
Oh, no. This is bad.

766
00:55:33,430 --> 00:55:35,330
What do I do?

767
00:55:53,580 --> 00:55:54,550
Wait.

768
00:55:56,580 --> 00:55:58,080
Hey, Yi-chan.

769
00:56:07,090 --> 00:56:09,430
Well, how did that happen?

770
00:56:09,790 --> 00:56:10,960
I'm sorry.

771
00:56:11,500 --> 00:56:15,170
Jae-in must have envied Si-woo
for his drone.

772
00:56:16,170 --> 00:56:19,870
I'll be sure to compensate enough
for the damage.

773
00:56:21,010 --> 00:56:23,580
The compensation isn't the point.

774
00:56:23,680 --> 00:56:24,910
Your child shouldn't have brought

775
00:56:24,980 --> 00:56:27,680
such an expensive drone to school
in the first place.

776
00:56:28,050 --> 00:56:30,650
This kind of accident was predictable.

777
00:56:32,420 --> 00:56:35,490
Are you blaming my child?

778
00:56:35,950 --> 00:56:38,020
That's just ridiculous!

779
00:56:38,490 --> 00:56:42,660
Ms. Cha, I ask you to follow
the rules of the school.

780
00:56:42,790 --> 00:56:46,160
Also, please set clear boundaries at home.

781
00:56:46,230 --> 00:56:48,270
What are you talking about?

782
00:56:48,330 --> 00:56:51,000
My child is a victim!

783
00:56:51,540 --> 00:56:55,570
But it's true that Si-woo broke
the school rules.

784
00:56:55,840 --> 00:56:58,980
We'll close the matter
by giving both Si-woo and Jae-in

785
00:56:59,480 --> 00:57:02,080
a proper warning.

786
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:07,950
Well, I believe we're done.

787
00:57:08,020 --> 00:57:09,520
Unbelievable.

788
00:57:09,850 --> 00:57:11,490
Does this make sense to you?

789
00:57:12,220 --> 00:57:15,130
That's enough. Don't make things worse.

790
00:57:15,190 --> 00:57:17,760
-Why should I...
-Do-yeong.

791
00:57:20,900 --> 00:57:24,170
Fine, I have to put up with it
because I'm a celebrity, right?

792
00:57:27,270 --> 00:57:28,340
Let's go.

793
00:57:45,720 --> 00:57:47,530
What took you so long?

794
00:57:47,590 --> 00:57:50,460
Ladies need more time.
Men should understand.

795
00:57:50,530 --> 00:57:52,230
You're just like your dad.

796
00:57:52,700 --> 00:57:54,030
Hold on, please.

797
00:57:56,770 --> 00:57:59,000
What is it? Aren't we done yet?

798
00:57:59,070 --> 00:58:00,310
Please apologize.

799
00:58:00,770 --> 00:58:03,010
It was rude of you to suspect Yi-chan

800
00:58:03,070 --> 00:58:05,380
and bring up what happened in the past.

801
00:58:05,580 --> 00:58:07,010
You owe us a proper apology.

802
00:58:16,120 --> 00:58:19,060
Yi-chan, I'm so sorry.

803
00:58:19,120 --> 00:58:22,190
I apologize for what happened today.

804
00:58:24,360 --> 00:58:25,460
Are you happy now?

805
00:58:25,930 --> 00:58:28,130
It's not like I did that on purpose.

806
00:58:31,370 --> 00:58:32,370
Let's go.

807
00:58:36,880 --> 00:58:37,940
Yi-chan.

808
00:58:38,440 --> 00:58:41,150
Did you keep quiet to protect Jae-in
back there?

809
00:58:41,550 --> 00:58:43,310
-Yes.
-You must've been upset.

810
00:58:43,380 --> 00:58:46,250
I didn't understand how you felt.
I'm sorry.

811
00:58:49,190 --> 00:58:50,360
That's my boy.

812
00:58:55,560 --> 00:58:58,360
Thank you for telling the truth.

813
00:58:58,430 --> 00:58:59,800
It must not have been easy.

814
00:58:59,860 --> 00:59:02,370
Don't mention it.
It was the right thing to do.

815
00:59:03,570 --> 00:59:06,270
Anyway, I'm relieved
that everything was settled in the end.

816
00:59:07,610 --> 00:59:10,780
Yi-chan, I'm sorry.

817
00:59:11,210 --> 00:59:12,440
It's okay.

818
00:59:21,190 --> 00:59:22,220
There you go.

819
00:59:23,220 --> 00:59:24,290
Oh, no.

820
00:59:31,800 --> 00:59:35,670
I believed
everything would be all right now.

821
00:59:36,530 --> 00:59:38,740
I moved here for Yi-chan's sake.

822
00:59:40,570 --> 00:59:42,840
But maybe I was being too laid back.

823
00:59:45,810 --> 00:59:47,410
You only just got here.

824
00:59:47,850 --> 00:59:50,220
The beginning is always the hardest.

825
00:59:51,380 --> 00:59:53,650
From now on,
don't keep everything to yourself

826
00:59:53,720 --> 00:59:55,490
or bottle everything up.

827
00:59:55,550 --> 00:59:58,860
When things get hard,
say so and ask for help.

828
00:59:59,390 --> 01:00:01,160
Learn to rely on others.

829
01:00:03,090 --> 01:00:06,860
You don't only have Yi-chan anymore.
You have me too.

830
01:00:09,200 --> 01:00:12,040
You're right. I have you too.

831
01:00:12,970 --> 01:00:15,370
Rely on me so I can rely on you too.

832
01:00:15,910 --> 01:00:18,110
Two is better than one, right?

833
01:00:24,080 --> 01:00:26,180
They seem to be having a blast.

834
01:00:26,250 --> 01:00:27,890
Jae-in is Yi-chan's first friend here.

835
01:00:27,950 --> 01:00:29,390
He's her first friend too.

836
01:00:34,290 --> 01:00:35,830
Should we be friends too?

837
01:00:37,730 --> 01:00:38,900
Should we do that?

838
01:00:40,570 --> 01:00:42,270
Stop being so polite with me.

839
01:00:43,030 --> 01:00:45,940
-Are we friends now?
-Sure.

840
01:00:46,470 --> 01:00:48,570
I guess.

841
01:00:54,780 --> 01:00:58,850
As you know, the foundation is paying
special attention to the child.

842
01:00:58,920 --> 01:01:02,590
Please make sure this kind of incident
never happens again, Mr. Han.

843
01:01:03,450 --> 01:01:06,890
One more thing. How is it going

844
01:01:06,960 --> 01:01:09,490
with the new teacher we talked about?

845
01:01:11,030 --> 01:01:12,360
From today?

846
01:01:12,930 --> 01:01:16,570
Then please schedule a meeting with me
within a few days.

847
01:01:27,950 --> 01:01:29,810
[CEO Nam Ji-seon]

848
01:02:02,010 --> 01:02:04,020
Who is it at this hour?

849
01:02:12,090 --> 01:02:15,990
[From Song Yeo-wool, To Song Yeo-wool]

850
01:02:16,060 --> 01:02:17,560
[From Song Yeo-wool]

851
01:02:38,320 --> 01:02:39,580
She didn't have to.

852
01:02:48,260 --> 01:02:50,060
[Hey, did you get home safely?]

853
01:02:50,130 --> 01:02:51,160
Yes.

854
01:02:52,060 --> 01:02:54,700
I'm really touched.

855
01:02:54,830 --> 01:02:56,970
When did you have time to send this?

856
01:02:57,240 --> 01:02:59,170
[What? What do you mean?]

857
01:02:59,270 --> 01:03:02,410
I mean the flowers. Thank you.

858
01:03:02,910 --> 01:03:05,180
You're the first person
besides my husband.

859
01:03:05,340 --> 01:03:06,410
[Flowers?]

860
01:03:07,040 --> 01:03:08,580
[It wasn't me.]

861
01:03:08,810 --> 01:03:10,150
What? It's not?

862
01:03:10,250 --> 01:03:12,880
[Wait a second. Someone sent you flowers?]

863
01:03:13,080 --> 01:03:15,350
[Who is it? A guy?]

864
01:03:16,020 --> 01:03:18,590
I thought it was you. Let me see.

865
01:03:19,290 --> 01:03:20,790
The message says...

866
01:03:21,930 --> 01:03:25,600
[I'm watching you.]

867
01:03:28,600 --> 01:03:31,300
I must've been mistaken.
I'll call you back.

868
01:03:39,780 --> 01:03:41,250
[Welcome to Woori Logistics.]

869
01:03:41,410 --> 01:03:44,780
[Our business hours are over
and we cannot take your call.]

870
01:03:45,220 --> 01:03:46,620
[Please call again...]

871
01:04:18,450 --> 01:04:22,390
[Unknown sender: Welcome home,
murderer Song Yeo-wool.]

872
01:05:31,920 --> 01:05:34,760
[Wujeong Capital]

873
01:05:44,670 --> 01:05:45,440
[Si-woo's mom]

874
01:06:29,080 --> 01:06:30,180
No way.

875
01:06:31,920 --> 01:06:32,980
Did she...

876
01:06:38,920 --> 01:06:41,190
Excuse me. Have you seen Yi-chan?

877
01:06:41,290 --> 01:06:44,330
Why are you looking for a boy
in the ladies' room?

878
01:07:19,060 --> 01:07:21,830
[High Class]

879
01:07:21,930 --> 01:07:25,300
You know the mothers have
high expectations, right?

880
01:07:25,370 --> 01:07:28,170
[It's an extremely special school.]

881
01:07:28,240 --> 01:07:30,140
[You shouldn't have moved here.]

882
01:07:30,210 --> 01:07:33,410
[If you're inexperienced and confused,
your kid will have a hard time.]

883
01:07:33,480 --> 01:07:35,780
-Why do you complain so much?
-It's a ticking bomb.

884
01:07:35,950 --> 01:07:37,480
[She was wearing this that day.]

885
01:07:37,550 --> 01:07:39,580
I never lost it.

886
01:07:39,650 --> 01:07:41,720
[Tell me the whole truth,]

887
01:07:42,090 --> 01:07:44,360
[or I'll tell everyone what I saw here.]

888
01:07:44,420 --> 01:07:46,420
[How can you blackmail me over this?]

889
01:07:46,620 --> 01:07:48,460
[It's not blackmail. It's a negotiation.]

